Round-3 review: most Round-2 items are locked, but Q15 still has a compile-shape blocker.

Q12 rlimits inconsistency: locked. RSS monitor is always-on observation; hard `setrlimit` is opt-in via `[agents] enforce_rlimits = true`; supervisor self-limit separately opt-in. Clean split.

Q5 UUID space: locked. Both slot and transport paths use UUID v4, stored in TOML, router maps `(slot_uuid, transport_uuid)` to handlers. Collision concern resolved.

Q9 Twilio signature: locked. All Twilio webhooks verify `X-Twilio-Signature` before processing, with 401 + audit on failure.

Q10 Origin allowlist: locked. Production requires explicit `allowed_origins`; empty means localhost-only; missing/non-allowlisted Origin gets 403 + audit.

Q11 OOM budget: locked. Handles both `137` and Python `MemoryError`; retry-budget exhaustion explicitly simulates 6 crashes in 60s, not one OOM.

Q14 PII clarity: locked. Secret/token/body redaction is clear; actor/target identifiers are intentionally logged as sensitive identifiers, not redacted. `alerts.log` has its own cap.

Q15 trait shape + graceful shutdown: **not locked yet**. Graceful shutdown text is good. But the trait shape as written is not object-safe:

```rust
pub trait WebhookHandler: Send + Sync {
    fn verify(&self, req: &WebhookRequest) -> Result<(), VerifyError>;
    async fn handle(&self, req: WebhookRequest) -> Response;
}
```

and then:

```rust
Box<dyn WebhookHandler>
```

`async fn` in a trait is not dyn-compatible/object-safe in this form. Same issue for `WsUpgradeHandler`. This will fail or force an implementation detail not stated.

Fix by locking one of these:

```rust
use futures::future::BoxFuture;

pub trait WebhookHandler: Send + Sync {
    fn verify(&self, req: &WebhookRequest) -> Result<(), VerifyError>;

    fn handle(&self, req: WebhookRequest) -> BoxFuture<'static, Response>;
}
```

or explicitly require `async_trait`:

```rust
#[async_trait::async_trait]
pub trait WebhookHandler: Send + Sync {
    fn verify(&self, req: &WebhookRequest) -> Result<(), VerifyError>;
    async fn handle(&self, req: WebhookRequest) -> Response;
}
```

Transport count wording: locked. The doc consistently clarifies 7 adapter families, with Slack having Socket + Events modes.

Phase 13 path: locked. Wizard lives under `plugins-core/skill-agent-wizard/SKILL.md`; legacy path avoided.

Overall: **NEEDS_FIX**. Only blocker is Q15 Rust trait object shape.

